article.headline: Oral Roberts 55, St. Louis 54
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Ken Tutt capped a 20-point game by hitting the game-winning 3-pointer from well beyond the arc with 10.5 seconds to go, giving Oral Roberts a 55-54 victory over Saint Louis on Saturday. Caleb Green had 13 points and six rebounds for Oral Roberts (3-0), which spoiled Saint Louis' home opener in the first meeting between the teams since the 1989-90 season. The Golden Eagles won despite 37.7 percent shooting and a season-low point total, but held Saint Louis to 30.8 percent. Oral Roberts has won consecutive non-conference road games for the first time since joining the Mid-Continent Conference in 1997-98. Tutt had all but one of Oral Roberts' five 3-pointers, going 4-for-7 from long range, and Luke Spencer-Gardner added 10 points, six assists and six rebounds. Reggie Bryant had 14 points and Izik Ohanon added 11 points and seven rebounds for Saint Louis (1-3), but Matt Gastel blocked Bryant's shot in the lane with about two seconds left in a bid for the win. The Billikens recovered from an eight-point second-half deficit before falling short. Bryant was just 5-for-16 from the field and Ohanon was 4-for-12. Tutt scored seven of his points in a 9-0 run that gave Oral Roberts the biggest lead by either team at 47-39 with 6:02 to go. Consecutive 3-pointers by Dwayne Polk in a 27-second span helped Saint Louis climb back into the game. Two free throws by Bryant gave Saint Louis a 53-52 lead with 56 seconds to go, and another free throw by Polk had made it a two-point cushion with 25.8 seconds left. Oral Roberts led 21-19 at the end of a first half characterized by poor shooting on both sides. Oral Roberts shot 22 percent, Saint Louis 23 percent.
